==法律与政治==
在法律上，消费者的概念的使用主要和[[消费者保护|消费者保护]]法有关，它的定义通常只限于活着的人（非集团或企业），不包括商业使用者。<ref>{{cite book |author=Krohn, Lauren |title=Consumer protection and the law: a dictionary |url=https://archive.org/details/environmentlaw00patt |publisher=ABC-CLIO |year=1995 |isbn=978-0-87436-749-2}}</ref>  典型的保护消费者的法律依据是以监管消费者和企业间不平等的议价能力等市场失灵和无效的观念为基础的。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://law.vanderbilt.edu/journals/journal/35-01/overby.htm|title=An Institutional Analysis of Consumer Law|accessdate=2007-01-29|publisher=Vanderbilt Journal of Transnational Law|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070302211417/http://law.vanderbilt.edu/journals/journal/35-01/overby.htm|archivedate=2007年3月2日|deadurl=yes}}</ref>  因为所有的潜在选民都是消费者，保护消费者明显有着重要的政治意义。

对消费者权益的关注不仅将消费者教育纳入了学校课程而且产生了大量的活动。{{Citation needed|date=2010年3月}} 还有各种各样的非盈利出版物，如旨在帮助消费者做决策教育消费者的《消费者报告》和《选择杂志》以及英国的《直达消费者》。

==公众反应==
尽管「消费者」这个词汇在政府、商业和媒体机构广泛使用，许多个人或群体会对这个标签产生反感，因为这个名称给他们指派了一个有限制的、被动的角色。<ref>{{cite web | title = Words to Avoid (or Use with Care). Because They Are Loaded or Confusing | url = http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/words-to-avoid.html#Consumer | accessdate = 2012-02-18 | archive-date = 2010-05-31 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100531084316/http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/words-to-avoid.html#Consumer | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Quotes on being a "Consumer" | url = http://www.mail-archive.com/www-archive@w3.org/msg04217.html | accessdate = 2012-02-18 | archive-date = 2020-07-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200724194011/https://www.mail-archive.com/www-archive@w3.org/msg04217.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title = Consumer. I hate the word: why Mediation is adding {{not a typo|it's}} voice to the call for a banning of the word Consumer| url = http://chrisstephenson.typepad.com/chrisstephenson/2009/07/consumer-i-hate-the-word-why-mediation-is-adding-its-voice-to-the-call-for-a-banning-of-the-word-con.html| accessdate = 2012-02-18| archive-date = 2020-08-05| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200805100226/https://chrisstephenson.typepad.com/chrisstephenson/2009/07/consumer-i-hate-the-word-why-mediation-is-adding-its-voice-to-the-call-for-a-banning-of-the-word-con.html| dead-url = no}}</ref>

